            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "@cpdean HTTPS is something the web server should do for you and therefore depends on your method of deployment. If we add HTTPS to the tutorial, we either end up with a lot of \"ifs\" in the tutorial or have to implicitly endorse one particular method. I don't think either is appropriate.\n\nAdding information about how to use HTTPS in the \"Deployment Options\" section, even just by linking to the documentation that covers this in the documentation of the respective server would probably be a good idea. We could then mention in which cases people should use HTTPS in the tutorial in a more abstract manner.\n"
        },
